    "1. Choose restaurant wisely - Look for healthier options that are low in sugar, sodium and saturated fats. \n\n2. Train your taste buds - Start replacing processed foods and snacks with healthier alternatives that contain more fiber, protein and essential vitamins. \n\n3. Keep healthy snacks on hand - Having a few healthy snacks with you at all times while traveling or eating out can help keep your hunger in check and ensure you don\u2019t overindulge. \n\n4. Stay hydrated - Drink plenty of water throughout the day and soda and sugary drinks should be avoided as much as possible.",
    "1. Establish time limits and have set times when you are not using digital devices; for example, no screens after 8 pm.\n\n2. Take regular breaks throughout the day from your digital devices; for example, set a timer every hour or two to remind you to step away from your devices for a few minutes.\n\n3. Find an alternate activity to engage in when you need a break from digital screens; for example, go for a walk, read a book, or take a yoga class.",
    "1. Eat more slowly. This allows time for your brain to realize when your stomach feels full. \n\n2. Eat without distractions. Put away the phone and laptop, and try to focus solely on the food. \n\n3. Try to make the activity of eating a mindful one. Pay attention to the smells, textures, and flavors.\n\n4. Savor your food. Focus on the experience of the meal and tune into the sensations of taste and pleasure.\n\n5. Set an intention before you eat.",
    "Of course! After workouts, aim for protein and carbs. Options include a protein smoothie, Greek yogurt with berries, a turkey or chicken wrap, or almonds with fruit. These aid energy replenishment and recovery.",
